WEBVTT

00:02.085 --> 00:04.463
MENDEZ: Carroll's execution's
the end of the month.

00:04.630 --> 00:07.930
- Joe, you been to see him?
- No. I moved on.

00:08.132 --> 00:09.976
You will too. As soon as we catch Mark.

00:10.177 --> 00:13.556
Why am I letting you guys have all the fun?
Let's go kill some people.

00:14.431 --> 00:18.311
This is all wrong. We have to make
this perfect. Or he'll kill us all.

00:18.519 --> 00:21.398
RYAN: Our boy Mark is punishing us
for killing his family last year.

00:21.605 --> 00:24.404
The scenes are recreations of the deaths.

00:24.608 --> 00:26.952
Second time in 24 hours
I've been called a liar.

00:28.445 --> 00:31.870
- First you're the liar. Now me.
- You lived this moment. You both did.

00:32.073 --> 00:34.327
It's a tableau of Max shooting Luke.

00:34.535 --> 00:35.912
Mark has followers now.

00:36.119 --> 00:38.463
Why is he writing "you've lied"
at every scene?

00:38.622 --> 00:41.341
- He's delusional.
- Hey. This is our revenge.

00:41.542 --> 00:43.340
I know. You're right. I'm sorry.

00:43.544 --> 00:45.717
Don't be sorry, little bro. Be angry.

00:45.921 --> 00:48.299
I was pushing you away.
I don't wanna do it anymore.

00:48.465 --> 00:50.934
- I need you.
- I need you too.

00:51.134 --> 00:53.557
I'm proud of you.
Tomorrow will be awesome.

00:53.720 --> 00:57.441
Because tomorrow, one of them dies.

01:24.668 --> 01:26.716
Big day, dude. This Andrew's truck?

01:26.920 --> 01:29.594
Yeah. We gotta get it off the street
now he's in custody.

01:29.756 --> 01:31.224
I'll take care of it.

01:38.807 --> 01:40.684
- Is everything ready?
- See for yourself.

01:49.318 --> 01:51.116
What do you think?

01:55.324 --> 01:56.951
Torture's not really my thing.

01:57.159 --> 01:59.207
That's why you need me.

01:59.411 --> 02:01.084
But you haven't seen...

02:02.706 --> 02:03.878
...the best part.

02:07.544 --> 02:09.545
- Is that...?
- Yes, sir.

02:09.755 --> 02:11.803
Bought it in Huntsville, Texas last year.

02:12.007 --> 02:17.355
Used in over 50 executions
between 1951 and 1970.

02:20.057 --> 02:23.937
Today we're gonna use it
to fry ourselves an FBI agent.

02:35.072 --> 02:36.574
[GRUNTING]

02:45.207 --> 02:46.925
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

02:47.793 --> 02:50.797
I'm sorry. Did I wake you up?

02:50.962 --> 02:54.557
- I thought I wore you out last night.
- Believe me, you did.

02:59.304 --> 03:01.853
Your hands are quick,
but your jab's a little weak.

03:02.057 --> 03:03.730
Oh, really?

03:04.893 --> 03:08.363
My high-school boyfriend was a boxer.
I used to patch him up after fights.

03:08.522 --> 03:11.696
- It's how I fell in love with medicine.
- How is it I don't know this?

03:11.900 --> 03:15.404
Well, six months isn't long enough
to reveal all our secrets.

03:15.612 --> 03:17.580
Tell me something
I don't know about you.

03:17.781 --> 03:18.953
Heh.

03:19.116 --> 03:21.039
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

03:21.868 --> 03:23.870
Saved by the bell.

03:26.456 --> 03:27.924
- Bad news?
- Good, actually.

03:28.125 --> 03:32.551
We got a fingerprint match on the guy that
threw blood on me. I gotta take a shower.

03:38.885 --> 03:40.603
My brother taught me how to fight.

03:41.221 --> 03:44.100
Guess he got tired of scraping me up
off the school yard.

03:44.725 --> 03:47.399
Lesson one was
never go looking for trouble.

03:47.561 --> 03:49.234
Lesson two...

03:49.396 --> 03:53.367
...when it's on,
do whatever it takes to win.

03:54.860 --> 03:56.407
I wish I could've met him.

03:57.112 --> 03:58.489
He would've liked you.

04:09.750 --> 04:11.627
Rise and shine.

04:11.877 --> 04:15.757
Eggs and oatmeal.
Protein and slow-releasing carbs.

04:16.005 --> 04:18.509
Plenty of energy for today's mayhem.

04:18.716 --> 04:20.264
I don't eat breakfast.

04:20.427 --> 04:23.601
Manners. This is very sweet, Mark.
Thank you.

04:23.764 --> 04:26.608
Do we need to go over anything?
Timing will be crucial today.

04:26.767 --> 04:29.145
No. We got it.

04:34.941 --> 04:37.615
I know you're upset
about Andrew's arrest.

04:39.780 --> 04:43.000
I am too. He brought us together.

04:45.285 --> 04:48.129
But he'd want us to keep our focus.

04:51.917 --> 04:55.967
Yeah. Of course. Okay?
You can count on us.

04:57.839 --> 04:59.307
Great.

05:00.634 --> 05:02.557
See you downstairs.

05:05.639 --> 05:08.939
- Ow. What's your problem?
- We have to keep him happy.

05:09.100 --> 05:10.647
That guy's a freak show.

05:10.852 --> 05:13.822
Bopping around the kitchen.
Talking to his dead brother.

05:13.980 --> 05:17.234
He'll gut us in our sleep if he even
suspects we have our own agenda.

05:18.235 --> 05:19.828
So just play nice.

05:32.999 --> 05:34.046
Hey, how you doing?

05:34.251 --> 05:36.845
How do you think?
Lot of innocent people died yesterday.

05:37.045 --> 05:38.513
Hey, Mike.

05:39.381 --> 05:41.850
Look. I don't wanna
square off with you, all right?

05:42.008 --> 05:45.512
- I know that you and Max... - Ancient
history. Don't even worry about it.

05:45.679 --> 05:47.022
Yeah?

05:47.222 --> 05:48.519
So we're cool?

05:48.682 --> 05:50.480
Sure. Cool.

05:52.769 --> 05:55.864
- Nice to see you're making friends.
- I'm not here to make friends.

05:56.898 --> 06:00.869
- What's Andrew doing here?
- We got a match on his real ID.

06:01.027 --> 06:04.201
Andrew Sharp. Turns out he's got
a wife and kids in Westchester.

06:04.364 --> 06:07.288
About a year ago,
Andrew walks out the door...

06:07.450 --> 06:09.703
...got into his truck, and disappears.

06:09.911 --> 06:13.040
- He's been listed as a missing person since.
- I sense a punch line.

06:13.248 --> 06:16.001
Before he left, Andrew got a call.
We checked the records.

06:16.209 --> 06:18.587
It originated in Layton, New Jersey.

06:19.129 --> 06:20.756
That's the last place we saw Mark.

06:20.922 --> 06:22.924
Andrew got the call
right after Mark escaped.

06:23.091 --> 06:24.434
He must have picked him up.

06:24.634 --> 06:26.762
- You got a few things you wanna ask?
- I do.

06:31.975 --> 06:33.727
RYAN:
Good morning, sunshine.

06:34.603 --> 06:37.322
I guess someone didn't
enjoy their first night in jail.

06:38.315 --> 06:41.615
So let me ask you something.
How could you do it?

06:41.818 --> 06:44.788
Just walk out on your wife and kids.
Never look back.

06:45.030 --> 06:47.408
You were married, what, 10 years?

06:47.574 --> 06:51.124
Witnessed the birth of your daughters.
Watched them grow up.

06:51.286 --> 06:52.629
To throw all that away...

06:52.829 --> 06:54.422
It's been hard.

06:55.457 --> 06:56.925
[SOBBING]
I miss them every day.

06:57.792 --> 07:01.092
You don't know how many times
I wanted to pick up the phone and...

07:04.174 --> 07:08.224
- Yeah. They were just camouflage. Heh.
- That's what I thought.

07:08.386 --> 07:10.605
WESTON:
But Mark is your real family, isn't he?

07:10.805 --> 07:13.274
That's why he called you,
why you picked him up.

07:13.433 --> 07:16.277
To protect him.
It meant throwing away your cover life.

07:16.436 --> 07:20.282
So, what's the connection?
My guess is Lily Gray?

07:20.482 --> 07:23.281
Did she see you as a potential father
for her boys?

07:23.485 --> 07:25.704
That why Mark trusted you
enough to call?

07:29.199 --> 07:31.076
Wow, am I supposed to clap
or something?

07:31.868 --> 07:34.166
Because really,
your insights are fairly obvious.

07:35.455 --> 07:36.707
May I offer a little advice?

07:37.290 --> 07:41.170
You're kind of sitting on the wrong side
of the table for it to hold much weight.

07:41.378 --> 07:43.801
But go ahead. Knock yourself out.

07:45.799 --> 07:48.097
Confess while there's still time.

07:50.887 --> 07:52.514
My conscience is clean.

07:53.139 --> 07:55.642
Clean or not,
until you tell the world what you did...

07:55.809 --> 07:57.527
...innocent people will keep dying.

07:58.311 --> 08:00.689
And their blood will be on your hands.

08:13.618 --> 08:15.370
What kind of fruit is that?

08:15.870 --> 08:19.249
- It's a melon.
- Well, yeah.

08:19.833 --> 08:23.679
I know. But what kind?
I always get them confused.

08:25.171 --> 08:27.048
It's a cantaloupe.

08:27.257 --> 08:28.725
I'm Jack.

08:29.175 --> 08:31.018
I'm married.

08:31.219 --> 08:33.847
Me too. So what?

08:35.515 --> 08:36.640
Bye, Jack.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.525
That was sad.

08:51.948 --> 08:54.872
Run DMV records. See what Andrew drove
when he disappeared.

08:55.076 --> 08:57.044
- Ryan.
- Hey.

08:57.245 --> 08:58.462
I'll catch up.

09:01.958 --> 09:05.383
- You all right? You don't look so good.
- I thought we were done with this.

09:05.587 --> 09:07.305
Yeah. So did I.

09:08.715 --> 09:11.389
Look, I don't think
I can go through with it again.

09:13.803 --> 09:16.602
Keep it simple in the hearing.
Stick to the script.

09:16.765 --> 09:19.109
- Got it.
- Don't raise your voice, don't get angry.

09:19.309 --> 09:24.065
Jeff, I'm fine. But honestly,
you seem like you're wound a little tight.

09:26.274 --> 09:28.402
- Is it that obvious?
- Mm-hm.

09:32.906 --> 09:37.002
You know, I asked Director Franklin
to let me run point on your covert op.

09:39.954 --> 09:41.297
No, I didn't know that.

09:41.498 --> 09:43.671
I knew that if all of
this stuff went south...

09:43.833 --> 09:46.928
...that I'd lose my job
or I'd even end up in prison.

09:47.087 --> 09:49.931
But Joe Carroll is a monster.
And so was Lily Gray...

09:50.090 --> 09:53.970
...and they had to be stopped by any means.
But now that the pressure is on...

09:55.512 --> 09:57.480
I can't sleep.

09:57.847 --> 10:00.942
I'm drinking all the time and...

10:02.769 --> 10:07.616
All right, I'm scared, Ryan. Okay?
What if it gets...?

10:09.025 --> 10:10.993
- Wait, I got...
- What's up? You okay?

10:11.194 --> 10:14.664
- Yeah. My chest is tight.
- Hang on. Come here.

10:14.864 --> 10:16.332
All right, here we go, buddy.

10:16.533 --> 10:19.787
We're going to the ER.
Take it easy, nice and easy.

10:21.121 --> 10:23.795
Hey. This is not all on you.

10:24.874 --> 10:27.753
Okay? I'll take the hit if I have to.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.138
I gotta get back in there.

10:31.297 --> 10:34.301
- We're on to something.
- Go. Get it done.

10:34.509 --> 10:37.012
- You good?
- I'm fine.

10:42.308 --> 10:45.027
Hey, according to the DMV,
Andrew's the registered owner...

10:45.270 --> 10:49.150
...of a 2006 silver pickup truck.
License plate number 4GF8891.

10:49.357 --> 10:52.156
All right. Let's put Big Brother to use.
Listen up.

10:52.318 --> 10:54.867
We're looking for a 2006 silver pickup.

10:55.071 --> 10:58.575
I want the plate number run through
every city camera as far back as we can.

10:58.783 --> 11:02.663
We find that truck, we find Mark.
Let's go. Come on.

11:11.045 --> 11:12.513
- We on schedule?
- Yes.

11:12.714 --> 11:15.217
Daisy and Kyle should be
making contact right now.

11:23.600 --> 11:26.228
Honey, what are you doing home?

11:27.937 --> 11:30.360
[CITIZEN COPE'S "HEALING HANDS"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

11:33.526 --> 11:34.869
[SIGHS]

11:35.028 --> 11:39.204
Heh. Well, it's a little early
in the day for wine.

11:39.782 --> 11:41.534
[CHUCKLES]

11:49.417 --> 11:51.715
You're not expecting
any of that to still fit.

11:54.047 --> 11:56.721
What are you up to, you bad boy?

12:04.224 --> 12:05.601
[GASPS]

12:06.267 --> 12:08.565
You really hurt my feelings
back there, you know?

12:18.863 --> 12:20.957
- Comfortable?
- Why are you doing this?

12:21.908 --> 12:23.330
Um...

12:23.493 --> 12:25.040
I wasn't held enough as a child.

12:25.495 --> 12:28.294
Or maybe it's because
my amygdala is underdeveloped.

12:28.831 --> 12:30.925
I'm gonna get some cantaloupe.
You want some?

12:31.125 --> 12:32.627
[GRUNTS]

12:33.002 --> 12:35.801
- Babe?
- No. I'm good. Thanks.

12:36.005 --> 12:39.384
- Okay. Time to call your husband.
- Why?

12:39.592 --> 12:42.937
- It's not a party without him, is it?
- I won't do it.

12:43.888 --> 12:45.731
Honey, I'm not asking.

12:47.183 --> 12:49.436
Say whatever you need to
to get him home.

12:50.353 --> 12:53.402
Give us away, and he'll get
your face in the mail. Got it?

13:01.698 --> 13:06.204
It's me. I'm sorry to do this,
but I just got a migraine.

13:06.828 --> 13:08.330
Can you come home?

13:08.538 --> 13:11.166
I know, but it's really bad.

13:12.792 --> 13:14.715
Okay. Thanks.

13:15.420 --> 13:17.138
I love you.

13:18.548 --> 13:23.270
Wow, you lied like a pro.
I bet he can't tell when you're faking it.

13:24.762 --> 13:26.105
Come on. We all do it.

13:27.223 --> 13:30.067
- How long have you been married?
- Sixteen years.

13:30.268 --> 13:34.944
That's incredible. How do you keep
it fresh? In the bedroom, I mean.

13:35.148 --> 13:36.616
Go to hell.

13:36.816 --> 13:39.660
Kyle and I do whatever we can
to keep the spark alive.

13:39.861 --> 13:42.990
- He's on his way yet?
- Yeah. I'd say we still got a half an hour.

13:43.740 --> 13:46.994
You wanna check her night table?
See if she's got anything naughty?

13:47.201 --> 13:48.578
- HeH, yeah.
- Heh.

13:49.620 --> 13:50.667
I'll be right back.

13:53.249 --> 13:55.968
Oh, God. I love him so much.

13:59.380 --> 14:00.973
That's it. We found the truck.

14:02.550 --> 14:03.597
Where?

14:03.801 --> 14:07.601
Traffic cam caught it entering a garage
in East Harlem this morning. Watch.

14:09.849 --> 14:11.817
I think that might be Mark.

14:12.018 --> 14:14.771
- Have HRT meet us there.
- I'm on it.

14:38.503 --> 14:39.629
Damn.

14:39.837 --> 14:42.010
- What's that?
- Silent alarm.

14:45.635 --> 14:48.479
- No. No. No.
- We gotta get you out of here.

14:48.679 --> 14:50.397
How'd that happen?

14:50.598 --> 14:52.191
Sewer pipe.

14:52.725 --> 14:54.477
Let's out a block away.

14:56.604 --> 14:59.904
- Wait. Wait. Wait. What about you?
- Don't worry about me.

15:10.701 --> 15:11.793
Okay. Let's go.

15:12.036 --> 15:13.083
We're in.

15:13.371 --> 15:14.714
Move.

15:57.248 --> 15:58.750
[GUNSHOT]

16:00.793 --> 16:03.512
- You all right?
- Better than him. Thanks.

16:03.713 --> 16:05.386
RYAN:
Shooter's down.

16:09.760 --> 16:11.012
This yours?

16:12.638 --> 16:15.391
Try holding on to it next time.

16:15.600 --> 16:17.773
MAX:
Ryan, get in here.

16:29.906 --> 16:31.499
It's Anna.

16:32.241 --> 16:33.914
Let's move.

16:37.955 --> 16:39.582
Anna? Baby, you down here...?

16:46.297 --> 16:48.391
I'll do whatever you want.

16:49.050 --> 16:51.519
Just don't hurt my wife.

16:52.428 --> 16:54.271
Sorry. We don't make deals.

16:55.139 --> 16:57.892
No! Don't hurt him. No.

16:58.100 --> 16:59.443
No.

17:00.645 --> 17:04.194
Sorry. Wish I could stay.
Suffocation's such a turn on.

17:16.786 --> 17:18.378
Anna.

17:22.083 --> 17:23.460
Oh, no.

17:23.667 --> 17:25.089
- Anna.
- Oh, my God.

17:27.880 --> 17:30.383
I need emergency medical
to 529 Cloverdale Drive.

17:30.591 --> 17:32.764
- Possible suffocation victim.
RYAN: Get her down.

17:37.890 --> 17:39.267
Come on, Anna.

17:39.433 --> 17:41.026
[RYAN GRUNTING]

17:45.648 --> 17:47.025
Come on.

17:50.987 --> 17:52.159
Come on.

17:54.448 --> 17:56.746
[GASPING THEN COUGHING]

17:59.161 --> 18:01.835
All right. Take a deep breath. You okay?

18:02.039 --> 18:03.666
Okay. We got you. We got you.

18:04.417 --> 18:06.761
They took Jeff.

18:06.961 --> 18:09.134
They took Jeff.

18:14.719 --> 18:15.766
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

18:15.928 --> 18:17.430
It's Mark.

18:18.139 --> 18:20.187
MARK [OVER PHONE]: They got Spider.
- What?

18:20.391 --> 18:22.610
The FBI raided the garage.
I barely got away.

18:22.810 --> 18:25.563
- What? What happened?
- How did they find you?

18:25.771 --> 18:27.990
How should I now?
You had a plan B, right?

18:28.190 --> 18:29.612
No, that's not a good idea.

18:30.067 --> 18:32.445
- You said he could do it.
- He can definitely do it.

18:32.612 --> 18:35.456
He... He just scares the hell out of me.

18:36.699 --> 18:38.542
We don't have a choice.

18:41.704 --> 18:43.331
What's going on?

18:45.249 --> 18:46.592
We have to call Neil.

18:52.089 --> 18:53.557
NEIL:
One more.

18:53.758 --> 18:55.476
Do I know you?

18:55.676 --> 18:57.394
I'm your son. Neil.

18:57.595 --> 18:59.347
No.

18:59.555 --> 19:02.229
My son is much younger.

19:04.852 --> 19:06.650
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

19:16.614 --> 19:19.037
I have to go out for a while.
Can you take over?

19:19.241 --> 19:21.619
Of course. I'll clean him up
and ready for bed.

19:21.827 --> 19:26.253
Thank you. Louise is gonna look after you for
a little while until I get back. Okay, Dad?

19:39.220 --> 19:40.642
[PANTING]

19:44.850 --> 19:48.195
Hey. You did great back there.

19:49.063 --> 19:52.533
I wanted it all to be perfect.
Now it's all messed up.

19:52.692 --> 19:54.820
No, it's not. It's not.

19:55.027 --> 19:57.780
You were smart. You had a backup plan.

19:58.781 --> 20:02.786
Question is, are you ready
for what has to be done next?

20:05.371 --> 20:07.840
You sure you can't help?

20:09.083 --> 20:13.384
I'm sorry, little bro.
You're gonna have to do this one alone.

20:13.921 --> 20:16.094
Just be strong.

20:17.925 --> 20:19.347
Okay.

20:19.552 --> 20:20.599
Okay.

20:23.889 --> 20:25.766
They dumped his cell phone
a block away.

20:25.975 --> 20:29.275
We're pulling footage. See if we
can identify what they're driving.

20:29.437 --> 20:32.987
- Gotta be the couple from the hotel.
- Taking them to that garage to be tortured.

20:33.149 --> 20:35.698
Which means they're looking
for a backup location now.

20:35.860 --> 20:38.158
We got a small window
before they go underground.

20:38.320 --> 20:39.822
We have an incoming Skype call.

20:40.698 --> 20:43.372
- It's Mark Gray.
- Trace it.

20:44.076 --> 20:45.749
Put it up on the screen.

20:50.166 --> 20:54.216
Gang's all here. Except Clarke.
I've got him.

20:54.378 --> 20:57.097
- What do you want?
MARK: I thought I made that very clear.

20:57.381 --> 20:59.884
Tell the truth, but you haven't.

21:00.050 --> 21:03.475
So here's the deal.
Go on television by 8:00 tonight.

21:03.679 --> 21:07.104
Tell the world
how you executed my mother.

21:07.433 --> 21:09.902
Or Clarke dies.

21:11.312 --> 21:13.440
- Any shot at a trace?
- Code's encrypted.

21:13.606 --> 21:15.449
Break the firewall. Just gonna take time.

21:15.608 --> 21:19.203
- Time we don't have.
- Send me that Skype image of Mark.

21:19.403 --> 21:21.781
We have less than five hours
to find Agent Clarke.

21:21.947 --> 21:24.416
I need us to go back through
everything that we have.

21:24.617 --> 21:27.416
The tableau murders,
the couple who took him, Andrew Sharp.

21:27.620 --> 21:31.124
We need to go through everything.
Figure out where they're holding him.

21:32.541 --> 21:35.135
What truth was he talking about?

21:35.920 --> 21:38.639
- His version of what happened.
- He's delusional.

21:38.839 --> 21:41.638
He can't cope with causing
the death of his family.

21:42.134 --> 21:44.011
Can't believe anything that psycho says.

21:46.806 --> 21:48.774
- Mendez knows.
RYAN: She doesn't know anything.

21:48.933 --> 21:49.980
She can't.

21:50.142 --> 21:52.315
Then let me put it a different way.
We know.

21:52.478 --> 21:57.154
- What's that supposed to mean?
- How long can we lie about Lily's shooting?

21:57.316 --> 22:00.570
- Mark Gray is in no position to judge us.
- Of course he's not.

22:00.778 --> 22:04.373
But don't we have to consider whether
coming clean is gonna help Clarke?

22:04.573 --> 22:07.952
No matter what we do,
there is no way that Mark lets him live.

22:08.160 --> 22:11.960
The only way to save Jeff is to find him.

22:26.053 --> 22:28.897
Where's Anna? Where's my wife?

22:29.181 --> 22:32.105
Facing death,
and all you're worried about is your girl.

22:32.309 --> 22:34.778
- I like that.
- Tell me she's okay.

22:36.480 --> 22:37.527
She's good.

22:38.190 --> 22:42.240
I can tell you guys have
something special, like me and Daisy.

22:45.781 --> 22:48.034
You ever cheat on Anna?

22:48.242 --> 22:50.870
- What?
- A lot of guys do.

22:51.078 --> 22:56.756
I never would. I mean, I get tempted,
because who doesn't, right?

22:58.294 --> 23:02.219
But I could never hurt Daisy like that.

23:02.423 --> 23:04.846
And I sure as hell
couldn't keep it from her.

23:05.050 --> 23:07.473
That girl can see right through me.

23:07.720 --> 23:09.393
What are you two gabbing about?

23:10.264 --> 23:11.857
How much we love our wives.

23:24.945 --> 23:26.663
MAX:
We got something.

23:26.864 --> 23:30.243
I was digging deeper into Andrew's past
looking for a connection to Mark.

23:30.451 --> 23:34.752
And what I found
is a connection to Joe Carroll.

23:35.331 --> 23:37.459
- What connection?
MAX: As a teenager...

23:37.625 --> 23:39.548
...he went to a school
near Lightford Academy.

23:39.710 --> 23:41.303
- Joe's boarding school.
MAX: Exactly.

23:41.462 --> 23:43.385
The two schools have shared instructors.

23:43.589 --> 23:47.389
Records show Andrew and Joe
had at least one class together.

23:51.096 --> 23:53.019
But if Andrew is one of Joe's followers...

23:53.182 --> 23:54.980
...why work with Mark?
- Mark hates Joe.

23:55.809 --> 23:58.733
Blames him for what happened
to his family as much as he blames us.

23:58.896 --> 24:02.776
- He wouldn't associate with Joe's followers.
- We have to make sense of all this.

24:03.525 --> 24:06.654
Ryan, you have to go see Joe.

24:09.990 --> 24:11.583
No. I'm done with him.

24:11.742 --> 24:12.959
- Ryan...
- No.

24:13.118 --> 24:15.416
- If he can give us a lead...
- We don't know that he can.

24:15.579 --> 24:18.298
Yeah. Well, we don't know that he can't.

24:18.499 --> 24:20.001
So let's find out.

24:21.794 --> 24:23.717
Clarke's life is on the line.

24:47.403 --> 24:50.407
- Where's the damn doctor?
- You really gotta try to relax...

24:50.572 --> 24:54.418
...because it's gonna put extra stress
on your heart. I know about this.

24:54.910 --> 24:58.289
- I'm worried about Anna.
- I left a message. I'm sure she's on her way.

24:59.289 --> 25:01.792
You know, I made her so many promises.

25:02.084 --> 25:05.258
We were supposed to go to Barcelona.
Go learn how to tango.

25:05.421 --> 25:08.265
- Tango?
- Yeah, well, shut up. Ha, ha.

25:08.424 --> 25:09.846
[CLARKE COUGHING]

25:11.760 --> 25:15.685
I keep telling her I'll do anything for
her. But the job keeps getting in the way.

25:16.181 --> 25:18.809
I'm sure she understands.
Job's important.

25:18.976 --> 25:21.479
Right now,
nothing's more important to me than her.

25:23.105 --> 25:24.357
[COUGHING]

25:25.774 --> 25:27.697
Just take it easy. Take it easy.

25:27.943 --> 25:32.039
Hello, nurse. Please, can we get
a little help in here, huh?

26:35.010 --> 26:36.637
Dr. Strauss.

26:36.845 --> 26:41.021
Agent Hardy. I wasn't expecting
to see you until my trial.

26:41.558 --> 26:44.186
- Come to wish me luck?
- I'm here about Andrew Sharp.

26:44.394 --> 26:45.896
Who?

26:48.524 --> 26:49.946
I made some calls.

26:51.068 --> 26:56.450
Andrew was in a class with Joe Carroll
that you taught at Lightford Academy.

26:56.657 --> 26:58.409
That was 30 years ago.

27:01.745 --> 27:03.668
He's prone to tears.

27:05.707 --> 27:07.584
I vaguely remember him.

27:08.210 --> 27:11.760
- An emotional child.
- Except it was all an act.

27:11.922 --> 27:17.179
And you knew it. My guess is that you
taught Andrew just like you taught Joe.

27:17.344 --> 27:21.565
How to hide his psychopathy,
camouflage it so he could fit in.

27:24.476 --> 27:27.946
Andrew's not one of Joe's followers,
is he?

27:28.605 --> 27:29.857
He's one of yours.

27:30.899 --> 27:33.652
I have no idea what you're talking about.

27:33.986 --> 27:35.078
Heh.

27:37.197 --> 27:41.998
Andrew has made himself some
very dangerous friends over the years.

27:46.331 --> 27:49.210
Well, they can be just about anybody.

27:49.418 --> 27:52.217
If you can tell me how to find them...

27:52.379 --> 27:57.180
...the prosecutor is prepared to amend
your attempted murder charges.

27:57.384 --> 27:58.806
And who knows?

27:58.969 --> 28:04.146
You could walk out of prison on your own
two feet instead of in a body bag.

28:04.808 --> 28:10.110
Hmm. First, you need to convict me,
Agent Hardy.

28:10.272 --> 28:13.776
And I like my chances at trial just fine.

28:14.526 --> 28:15.618
[CHUCKLES]

28:16.028 --> 28:18.702
- That's funny.
- Pardon?

28:18.906 --> 28:22.001
Well, you didn't even ask me
what Andrew did.

28:22.284 --> 28:26.130
- You're not curious?
- Not my concern.

28:26.288 --> 28:27.790
I will offer you this.

28:28.373 --> 28:30.421
From what I remember of him...

28:30.626 --> 28:35.632
...Andrew would need
a very powerful motivating factor...

28:35.839 --> 28:39.685
...to do anything that would have drawn
the attention of the FBI.

28:40.636 --> 28:41.933
Devotion?

28:42.095 --> 28:44.268
I was thinking...

28:45.307 --> 28:46.854
...fear.

28:49.770 --> 28:51.238
How's Joe?

28:54.691 --> 28:56.364
I wouldn't know.

28:56.818 --> 28:58.695
Oh, you two broke up?

29:00.989 --> 29:02.662
You miss him?

29:32.938 --> 29:34.815
How much longer?

29:38.402 --> 29:39.870
How much longer?

29:40.737 --> 29:42.535
I don't like to be rushed.

29:43.365 --> 29:44.742
KYLE:
No.No.No.

29:45.200 --> 29:49.501
Take your time, brother.
Not like we're on the clock or anything.

29:52.291 --> 29:53.508
[CLARKE GRUNTS]

29:53.875 --> 29:55.468
Kyle.

30:44.593 --> 30:47.767
Okay. Seven. Seven.

30:47.929 --> 30:49.476
Five...

30:53.352 --> 30:55.696
So did you get anything from
Strauss we can run on?

30:55.896 --> 30:59.366
He confirmed his connection to Andrew.
Nothing else. Hang on.

30:59.524 --> 31:02.277
- Hello.
- Ryan, it's me.

31:02.486 --> 31:04.909
Jeff. Put a trace on this.

31:06.365 --> 31:08.663
- Where are you?
CLARKE [OVER PHONE]: I don't know.

31:08.825 --> 31:12.079
- Anna. Is she...?
- Anna's good. She's fine.

31:12.245 --> 31:15.169
She's worried. Take a look around,
and tell me what you see.

31:15.332 --> 31:19.132
I'm in a warehouse, I think.
Or a factory or something. It's abandoned.

31:19.336 --> 31:21.589
Okay. How did you get there?

31:21.755 --> 31:26.010
They tied me up. They threw me in a van.
There were no windows. I couldn't get...

31:26.218 --> 31:28.687
And how long were you driving? Jeff?

31:31.139 --> 31:33.437
Hello? Clarke, you there? Hello?

31:39.731 --> 31:41.904
- Did you find him?
- Working on triangulating.

31:42.651 --> 31:46.952
Looks like the call emanated from
Pennsylvania, Reading area.

31:47.155 --> 31:49.203
- I'm going.
- I'll get you backup.

32:12.431 --> 32:13.774
[GRUNTS]

32:42.043 --> 32:45.547
Agent Hardy.
We have vehicles on site for your team.

32:45.714 --> 32:49.594
We'll assist your search any way we can.
But that cell tower covers 15 square miles.

32:49.801 --> 32:52.395
Target needs privacy.
Abandoned factory. Warehouse.

32:52.596 --> 32:55.224
We got a lot of that,
but we'll pull together a list.

33:07.027 --> 33:08.574
[GROANS]

33:17.287 --> 33:19.961
Hey there, buddy. Wakey-wakey.

33:21.208 --> 33:23.631
What you want first,
the good news or the bad news?

33:23.835 --> 33:26.008
I don't care about either one.

33:26.213 --> 33:28.841
Come on. Don't be so negative.

33:29.090 --> 33:33.891
Okay, bad news first. Looks like
your friends did not come through for you.

33:34.095 --> 33:37.190
- What are you talking about?
- Their deadline to confess the truth.

33:37.349 --> 33:41.274
- I don't think they're gonna make it.
- I don't think it's anything personal.

33:41.728 --> 33:42.775
The good news...

33:43.688 --> 33:45.611
...you could save yourself, Romeo.

33:46.024 --> 33:48.743
I don't have anything to confess.

33:50.362 --> 33:53.832
Please. Please reconsider that.

34:00.956 --> 34:03.880
I was a bit rushed, but I'm satisfied.

34:04.960 --> 34:09.887
The dimensions have been carefully
calculated to be exactly the right size.

34:10.090 --> 34:11.637
For what?

34:13.385 --> 34:14.637
To put you in.

34:16.263 --> 34:18.139
- What?
KYLE: Yeah.

34:18.348 --> 34:20.350
That was my reaction too.

34:22.811 --> 34:24.529
Wait.

34:24.728 --> 34:26.322
What the hell is that?

34:26.523 --> 34:32.656
This is a pithing needle used on cattle.
I'll insert it in the base of the skull.

34:34.906 --> 34:38.501
You'll be paralyzed, but fully conscious.

34:38.702 --> 34:41.545
Then I'll dislocate your joints.

34:41.913 --> 34:43.290
One at a time.

34:44.916 --> 34:48.545
That'll allow me to fold your body,
limb by limb, on top of itself.

34:52.424 --> 34:54.552
You'll be aware every moment.

34:56.052 --> 35:01.479
Hopefully, you'll appreciate the artistry
in what you are experiencing.

35:10.692 --> 35:13.115
Hey. Tom just called in.

35:13.320 --> 35:15.869
- Didn't find anything at his location.
- Damn it.

35:16.072 --> 35:18.541
Ryan, it's almost 8.

35:18.742 --> 35:19.789
I know. I know.

35:20.702 --> 35:23.501
If we give Mark what he wants,
it could buy us more time.

35:28.418 --> 35:30.341
- Mike.
- Hey, found something.

35:30.545 --> 35:32.218
Abandoned industrial park
off route seven.

35:32.380 --> 35:35.008
Local P.D. said
they saw cars pulling in today.

35:35.216 --> 35:38.220
Abandoned industrial park, route seven.

35:38.762 --> 35:42.483
- Here. Two minutes.
- All right. Two minutes. We're on our way.

35:57.364 --> 36:01.665
All right. Split up. Two-man teams.
Stay focused, people.

36:01.826 --> 36:02.918
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

36:03.078 --> 36:05.376
- Take your team. Let's go.
- Gina, we're close.

36:05.580 --> 36:08.174
Ryan, a video just came through.

36:08.375 --> 36:11.094
You need to see it.
It's streaming on the Internet.

36:11.336 --> 36:13.464
I'm sending it to you now.

36:16.174 --> 36:19.018
My name is Jeffrey Clarke.

36:19.219 --> 36:24.851
I'm a Special Agent
with the New York office of the FBI.

36:25.433 --> 36:27.527
I have a confession to make.

36:28.603 --> 36:35.327
I sanctioned an FBI black-ops unit
led by Agent Ryan Hardy.

36:35.985 --> 36:38.283
The laws were broken.

36:39.531 --> 36:41.158
People were killed.

36:42.867 --> 36:44.995
Lily Gray was executed in cold blood.

36:48.456 --> 36:51.881
I am confessing to these crimes.

36:52.502 --> 36:55.597
And I seek absolution that I know...

36:57.048 --> 36:59.142
...I don't deserve.

37:00.635 --> 37:05.607
KYLE: Thank you, Agent Clarke, for doing
what your friends were too cowardly to do.

37:11.563 --> 37:13.065
Come on. We're out of time.

37:52.437 --> 37:54.656
- They shot the video here.
- He's gotta be close.

39:06.803 --> 39:08.680
Did he suffer much?

39:08.888 --> 39:10.811
Medically speaking,
it's impossible to know.

39:10.974 --> 39:12.772
You didn't answer the question.

39:14.978 --> 39:16.651
He was, no doubt, in shock.

39:17.188 --> 39:21.989
Hopefully, consciousness
or any pain was mercifully brief.

39:45.383 --> 39:48.387
Now, you try and sleep now, okay?

39:50.179 --> 39:52.398
Thanks, Neil.

40:02.525 --> 40:04.903
People were killed.

40:06.029 --> 40:08.953
Lily Gray was executed in cold blood.

40:09.449 --> 40:12.794
I am confessing to these crimes.

40:13.661 --> 40:17.040
And I seek absolution that I know...

40:18.416 --> 40:20.589
...I don't deserve.

40:21.044 --> 40:22.762
Pretty good, huh?

40:23.338 --> 40:26.387
Yeah, fine. I should have been there.

40:26.966 --> 40:30.186
There's nothing we would've wanted more.
It didn't work out that way.

40:30.345 --> 40:35.567
I want to look in his lying face but the
FBI got on to Spider. How'd that happen?

40:35.767 --> 40:38.316
You're lucky you're not dead like Spider.

40:39.145 --> 40:41.068
What did you say?

40:41.773 --> 40:44.617
I hear whining
when I should hear "thank you."

40:44.776 --> 40:46.995
- Shut up, Kyle.
- That's how you talk to me?

40:48.655 --> 40:50.828
Take it easy, man.
I didn't mean anything by...

40:52.575 --> 40:58.582
- Don't ever speak to my brother like that.
- No, Mark. Don't kill him. You need us.

40:58.748 --> 41:01.217
[GRUNTING]

41:11.427 --> 41:13.350
[COUGHING]

41:38.454 --> 41:40.923
I'll be dead by the time
the damn doctor gets here.

41:41.124 --> 41:44.253
Ornery. I like that. More of that.

41:44.877 --> 41:47.881
Hi. Sorry for the wait.
I'm really backed up today.

41:48.089 --> 41:49.762
It's no problem. He's only dying.

41:49.966 --> 41:53.641
- I thought you said I was fine.
- Let me be the judge of that.

41:59.350 --> 42:02.069
Well, good news. You're alive.

42:02.270 --> 42:05.570
Your heartrate's a little high but steady.
We like that.

42:05.732 --> 42:06.779
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

42:06.983 --> 42:09.657
I'm gonna run an EKG.
But I think you're gonna be okay.

42:11.237 --> 42:12.659
Thanks, doc.

42:13.281 --> 42:15.033
My pleasure.

42:38.222 --> 42:40.270
[SOBBING]

43:38.449 --> 43:40.451
[English - US - SDH]
